  "text": "Our remedy for brittleness around ties (P2) is inspired by the triplet loss [CITATION_1] ; we introduce a shift in the scores during training in order to induce a margin. In particular, we add a negative shift to the positively labeled scores and positive shift the negatively labeled scores as illustrated in Fig. 3 . This also implicitly removes the destabilizing scale-invariance. Using notation as before, we modify the scores as",
